N2  - Overall Brief Description: We will present novel non-invasive neuromodulation interventions in Alzheimer's disease (AD). • Prof. dr. Maarten Van Den Bossche on the first trial of closed-loop acoustic stimulation to enhance slow wave sleep in AD. • Prof. dr. Maria Lapid on Intermittent Theta Burst Stimulation in Mild Cognitive Impairment • Prof. dr. Willem de Haan on tDCS/tACS in AD and computational models to simulate stimulation. Learning Objective #1: By the end of this presentation, participants will comprehend the rationale behind closed-loop acoustic stimulation for enhancement of slow wave sleep and have insight in the key findings of a first trial in Alzheimer's disease. Learning Objective #2: By the end of this presentation, participants will understand the design of the iTBS study in MCI and the key findings from the preliminary results. Learning Objective #3: By the end of this presentation, participants will appreciate the possibilities of tDCS/tACS in Alzheimer's disease and computational models to simulate stimulation.
