N2  - Abstract Objectives: Individuals with isolated rapid eye movement sleep behavior disorder (iRBD) are susceptible to cognitive decline, which is often linked to dysfunction in posterior brain regions. Transcranial direct current stimulation (tDCS) has the potential to modify cortical excitability, and high-definition tDCS (HD-tDCS) can specifically target regional neural activity and enhance cognitive function. This single-blind pilot study aimed to investigate whether HD-tDCS applied to the right posterior parietal cortex could improve overall cognitive function in iRBD patients with mild cognitive dysfunction. Methods: A single-blind, randomized, sham-controlled pilot trial was conducted involving eight participants with iRBD with mild cognitive dysfunction [Montreal Cognitive Assessment (MoCA) score 19-26]. The central anode was positioned over the right posterior parietal cortex (P4), and the four surrounding cathodes were placed over Pz, C4, P8, and O2. Participants were randomly assigned to receive either HD-tDCS (20 minutes of 2mA for five consecutive days) or sham stimulation. A sleep questionnaire, the MoCA, and electroencephalography during the Posner task were administered before and after one month of stimulation. Results: The median age of participants was 73 years, and 5 (62.5%) were female. The median MoCA score was 24 (range 22-25). Right posterior parietal HD-tDCS was safe and well-tolerated. The MoCA score tended to increase from a median of 23.5 to 26.5 in the stimulation group only (p=0.068). Reaction time during the Posner task decreased regardless of condition, but only in the stimulation group (p=0.068). No significant changes were observed in ERP parameters. Conclusion: The findings of this pilot study indicate that HD-tDCS applied to the right posterior parietal cortex is safe and may potentially improve overall cognitive function in individuals with mild cognitive impairment associated with iRBD. A larger-scale clinical trial with a cross-over design is needed to definitively validate HD-tDCS as a treatment option for cognitive impairment in iRBD. Research Category and Technology and Methods Translational Research: 9. Transcranial Direct Current Stimulation (tDCS) Keywords HD-tDCS, REM sleep behavior disorder, Cognition, Event related potential
