N2  - Symposium title Repetitive Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation (rTMS) to ameliorate symptoms of schizophrenia spectrum disorders Abstract Schizophrenia is a chronic psychiatric disorder that severely affects patients’ functioning and quality of life. Schizophrenia’s core features include positive and negative symptoms and cognitive impairments. Unlike positive symptoms, cognitive impairment and negative symptoms cannot be treated pharmacologically and represent consistent predictors of the illness’s prognosis. Nonsocial and social cognitive interventions have been developed to target these symptoms, providing heterogeneous results. Additionally, non-invasive brain stimulation techniques such as transcranial magnetic stimulation have received attention as an alternative to reduce schizophrenia symptoms. In our pilot study, we combined intermittent theta burst stimulation (iTBS) with cognitive training to improve negative symptoms and cognitive impairment in schizophrenia spectrum patients. Out of one hundred eligible patients invited to take part in the study, twenty-one agreed. We randomly assigned the participants to one out of four groups, in which the stimulation condition (real vs. sham iTBS) and cognitive intervention (no training vs. training) were manipulated. The participants received fifteen iTBS sessions (one daily session from Monday to Friday) targeting the left dorsolateral prefrontal cortex over a three-week period. After each stimulation session, participants received (or did not receive) a 50-minute training according to the assigned condition. Consensus-based clinical and cognitive assessments were conducted at five time points: before and immediately after the treatment and at three follow-ups at one, three, and six months after the treatments’ end. Preliminary data show a marginal modulation of iTBS on negative symptoms, whereas the training improved isolated cognitive functions. The methodological strengths and limitations of the study will be discussed. Research Category and Technology and Methods Clinical Research: 10. Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation (TMS) Keywords schizophrenia, iTBS, cognitive interventions, combined treatments
