N2  - Background: Schizophrenia is a complex psychiatric disorder with cognitive deficits that significantly impact functional outcomes. Objectives: Evaluate the efficacy of high-frequency rTMS in managing cognitive symptoms in schizophrenia, Assess the overall efficacy of high-frequency rTMS in schizophrenia treatment. Methods: Stable schizophrenia patients (ICD-10 criteria) on a fixed dose of antipsychotics for ≥4 weeks were assessed using the Montreal Cognitive Assessment (MoCA), Positive and Negative Syndrome Scale (PANSS), and Clinical Global Impression (CGI) scores at baseline, after 10 rTMS sessions, and 4 weeks post-treatment. Patients received 10 sessions of rTMS on alternate days (20 Hz frequency, 20,000 pulses per session). Results: Improvement in cognitive and overall schizophrenia symptoms was observed after rTMS, with sustained benefits at follow-up.
